  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half and wash carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice very finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once melted, add the<strong> sliced leek</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and 30ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [60ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong>, then cook for 5 min or until the water has evaporated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> (skins on) in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the skin off the<strong> smoked mackerel fillet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and discard</p><p>Flake the <strong>smoked</strong> <strong>mackerel</strong> into very small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine the<strong> flaked mackerel </strong>in a large bowl with the <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>cooked leek</strong>, reserve the pan</p><p>Season with a pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, knead well and divide the mixture into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>then shape into patties – these are your<strong> smoked mackerel fishcakes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a low heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>smoked mackerel</strong> <strong>fishcakes</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side until browned and crispy, adding more <strong>vegetable oil</strong> if needed</p><p>Tip: Flip gently and resist moving the patties so they hold their shape!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1765.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
